	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, May 15th 6:01 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>202 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>How much would it sell for?&nbsp;&nbsp;Frankly, I have no idea as I've never bought one, looted one, or sold one.  I have two wonderful suggestions for you though, Gamm.  Remember how I told you I found the weapon on this very site?  Well, if you follow those steps you will be able to click the link to see the weapon in detail and therein you will find an average price.  Typically, this site is wildly inaccurate for prices but it might give you a general idea.<br><br>Secondly, for a much more reliable price check, zone into the bazaar and do a search for your weapon there.  Prices differ by server quite a bit, so your server might have a much different price than another server.<br><br>What weapon do I recommend?  Weapon??  Enchanters generally don't weild weapons a whole lot, at least not for the sake of using them in melee.  They mostly sit back, cast, and stay far enough away from the mobs that they don't get beaten to a pulp.  I'm gonna give you another piece of advice here Gammo.  Do an equipment search by slot, again on this very site, and narrow it down to primary slot items that are enchanter usable.  If it were me, I'd be looking for items with INT, mana, maybe CHA on it.  Stein of moggok is something you can quest for yourself at level 12 as an enchanter.  Look that up ... also here on this very site.<br><br>I'm trying to teach you to fish here Gammo, work with me ...</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
