	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=169731><span id= >randalin</span></a><br><span id=notbold>58 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.02]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Suggestions for the Bazaar.<br><br>If you have a lot of lag in the bazaar, I suggest the following steps (It was the only way my wife's PC could handle the bazaar before the upgrade.)<br><br>before zoning in:<br>Filter off all unneeded chat.<br>Particle effects OFF.<br>Clip Plane as low as you can go.<br>Look at least 60 degrees down.&nbsp;&nbsp;(the less you see of other folks, the better)<br><br>Once inside:<br>Face an outside wall that points you AWAY from the heart of the zone.<br><br>use the /bazaar command to search for what you want.  Right click the merchant you want to point toward them.  With a little practice (esp easy with LOY map) you'll be navigating the bazaar to your desired merchants with little difficulty and only notice lag when you have to look up to find them when there are multiple merchants in front of you.  (I usually would have her look up enough to see their feet.  a / &lt;name&gt; helps 'cause if they're a troll, then look for troll feet, etc.)<br><br>Worst case scenario, you spend a minute extra finding them, and getting to your trade.  But if you DON'T take these steps, how long would it take you to find the item and get to them?<br><br>Hope this helps.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
